# Accessibility Baseline

Accessibility is required for all new UI.

## Rules

- Use semantic landmarks where applicable: `header`, `nav`, `main`, `section`, `footer`.
- Icon-only buttons/links must have an accessible name (`aria-label` or visible text).
- Keep heading hierarchy logical (`h1` then `h2`, etc.).
- Ensure keyboard users can reach and operate interactive elements.
- Use visible focus styles (do not remove focus outline without replacement).
- Prefer Testing Library role-based queries in tests (`getByRole`) to enforce accessible markup.

## Navigation/anchors

- Every `href="#section-id"` must map to an existing element with `id="section-id"`.
- Sticky header pages should use section scroll offset (`scroll-mt-*`) to prevent clipped headings.
